@node f_clearproject "F_ClearProject" 

@{b}@{u}F_ClearProject@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}Name: @{ub}  F_ClearProject -- clear the active Project 

@{b}Synopsis: @{ub}  F_ClearProject Force/S 

@{b}Function: @{ub}  Deletes all data in the current project. It will be in a 
   state much like after a New.  If you do not specify Force, this 
   command does exactly the same as @{"Project/Erase" Link MnErase}. That means, it is 
   possible, that a requester opens, which asks you whether you want to 
   save the current project before proceeding or cancel.  To prevent 
   this, specify the Force parameter. This will suppress all warnings. To 
   find out, wheter the project is not saved, you may use @{"F_IsVirgin" Link F_IsVirgin}.  

@{b}Inputs: @{ub}  Force -- suppress all warnings  

@{b}Results: @{ub}  none 

@{b}See also: @{ub}  Project/Erase, @{"F_IsVirgin" link F_IsVirgin}, @{"F_MakeVirgin" link F_MakeVirgin} 

@endnode 
